To sound, take advantage of calms or of good weather, when the sea is not rough, and when the drift of the ship will not be rapid, and sound from the weather gangway, or from a boat lowered for the purpose. ,Let the shot or lead take the twine as fast as it will, as the chip does the log line, and carefully note the time as the line goes out, by the 400, the 600 and the 1,000 fathom marksl* Note also the drist, and every cir- cumstance connected with the operation, and enter them upon the log, stating in every instance of losS, the quantity of twine lost, and the quantity remaining on the reel.
